{
  "texts": [
    "During a call to the API, the developers must comply with the constraints of API calls.",
    "Otherwise, API misuse can occur, leading to serious software security issues, such as NULL pointer dereference, pointer use after free, and logical bugs.In recent years, many researchers have used text analysis to find various security problems automatically, including access control configuration errors, wrong access requests, and logic flaws.",
    "For example, application developers provide privacy policies and notify users, but users cannot tell whether the application's natural behavior is consistent with their privacy policies.",
    "In response to this problem, Zimmeck et al. [466] proposed a systematic solution to automate the analysis of privacy policies to detect inconsistencies between them and application-specific behavior.",
    "Tools such as WHYPER [467] and AUTOCOG [468] examine whether Android applications correctly describe usage permissions in application descriptions."
  ]
}